            <p>&#8212;The little head in oil, with hat (of Elias Hicks)<ptr target="n4265"/> sent me from Richmond
                Indiana painted by Sidney Morse<ptr target="duk.00863_n3"/>&#8212;As I understand it <add rend="supralinear"
                    >is</add>was from a photo, or daguerreotype of Elias, from life, taken about
                1828 or '29 there.<ptr target="loc.03180_n2"/><add rend="pasteon"><p>Morse's
                        letter</p><p>Richmond Indiana</p><p>Jan 31. 1888</p><p>..."a little sketch
                        in oil (on a box cover) from an old photo of a steel engraving brought me by
                        a Mr. Harris<ptr target="n5001"/> who heard Elias preach when he was 10 years old. He says my
                        copy [this picture] is quite as good as the original. I don't think so
                        myself; but it approximates."<ptr target="loc.03180_n3"/></p></add></p>
